
Overview of noun chill

The noun chill has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (3) chill, iciness, gelidity -- (coldness due to a cold environment)
2. (2) frisson, shiver, chill, quiver, shudder, thrill, tingle -- (an almost pleasurable sensation of fright; "a frisson of surprise shot through him")
3. (1) chill, shivering -- (a sensation of cold that often marks the start of an infection and the development of a fever)
4. chill, pall -- (a sudden numbing dread)

Overview of verb chill

The verb chill has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) chill -- (depress or discourage; "The news of the city's surrender chilled the soldiers")
2. (1) cool, chill, cool down -- (make cool or cooler; "Chill the food")
3. cool, chill, cool down -- (loose heat; "The air cooled considerably after the thunderstorm")
